                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d392">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. No. 837.2222/5</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Cuba</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GWE1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gonzales</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-07-13T13:00:00-05:29">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 13, 1918, 1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 4.37 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The bill giving President powers somewhat similar to those delegated in our
                    Trading with Enemy Act has passed both Houses, being forced through by Executive
                    against consistent Liberal opposition. Obligatory military service act also
                    passed both Houses, but amendments are to be considered. The Liberals contested
                    every step.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_GWE1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Gonzales</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
